# Dataset Documentation

## Table: `drivers`

**Description:**  
This table contains demographic, licensing, and employment information about company drivers. Each row represents one driver.

**Grain:**  
One row = one driver.

---

## Columns

| Column Name        | Data Type        | Description                                             | Example        | Notes |
|--------------------|------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|---------------|------|
| `driver_id`        | String           | Unique identifier assigned to each driver              | DRV00001      | Primary key for this table |
| `first_name`       | String           | Driver’s first name                                    | Jennifer      | — |
| `last_name`        | String           | Driver’s last name                                     | Hernandez     | — |
| `hire_date`        | Date             | Date the driver was hired by the company               | 2014-10-31    | Used to calculate tenure |
| `termination_date` | Date (nullable)  | Date employment ended, if applicable                   | 2021-05-17    | Blank if driver is still employed |
| `license_number`   | String           | Driver’s license number                                | DL673510887   | Potentially sensitive (PII) |
| `license_state`    | String           | State where the license was issued                     | WA            | US state abbreviation |
| `date_of_birth`    | Date             | Driver’s birth date                                    | 1973-11-07    | Can be used to calculate age |
| `home_terminal`    | String           | Primary terminal/location assigned to the driver       | Denver        | Operational location |
| `employment_status`| String           | Current employment state                               | Active        | Expected values: Active, Terminated |
| `cdl_class`        | String           | Commercial Driver’s License class                      | A             | Indicates vehicle qualification level |
| `years_experience` | Integer          | Years of professional driving experience               | 3             | May include experience before hire |

---

## Table: `trucks`

**Description:**  
This table contains identification, technical specifications, and operational status information for company trucks. Each row represents one truck.

**Grain:**  
One row = one truck.

---

## Columns

| Column Name               | Data Type | Description                                              | Example             | Notes |
|---------------------------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------|---------------------|------|
| `truck_id`                | String   | Unique identifier assigned to each truck                 | TRK00001            | Primary key for this table |
| `unit_number`             | Integer  | Internal fleet unit number                               | 3463                | Operational tracking ID |
| `make`                    | String   | Truck manufacturer                                       | Peterbilt           | — |
| `model_year`              | Integer  | Year the truck model was manufactured                    | 2016                | Used to assess vehicle age |
| `vin`                     | String   | Vehicle Identification Number                            | 1VV205190335317039   | Unique vehicle identifier (PII-sensitive asset data) |
| `acquisition_date`        | Date     | Date the truck was acquired by the company               | 2017-04-27          | Used for lifecycle analysis |
| `acquisition_mileage`     | Integer  | Mileage on the truck at time of acquisition              | 18814               | Baseline mileage |
| `fuel_type`               | String   | Type of fuel used by the truck                           | Diesel              | — |
| `tank_capacity_gallons`   | Integer  | Maximum fuel tank capacity in gallons                    | 200                 | Impacts route range |
| `status`                  | String   | Current operational status of the truck                  | Active              | Example values: Active, Maintenance |
| `home_terminal`           | String   | Primary terminal/location assigned to the truck          | Omaha               | Operational base |

---

## Table: `trailers`

**Description:**  
This table contains identification, specifications, and operational status details for company trailers. Each row represents one trailer.

**Grain:**  
One row = one trailer.

---

## Columns

| Column Name          | Data Type | Description                                             | Example             | Notes |
|----------------------|----------|---------------------------------------------------------|---------------------|------|
| `trailer_id`         | String   | Unique identifier assigned to each trailer              | TRL00001            | Primary key for this table |
| `trailer_number`     | Integer  | Internal fleet number used to identify the trailer      | 4290                | Operational tracking ID |
| `trailer_type`       | String   | Type of trailer based on cargo capability               | Refrigerated        | Example values: Dry Van, Refrigerated |
| `length_feet`        | Integer  | Length of the trailer in feet                           | 53                  | Standard trailer size indicator |
| `model_year`         | Integer  | Year the trailer model was manufactured                 | 2016                | Used to assess equipment age |
| `vin`                | String   | Vehicle Identification Number for the trailer           | 1AV889081755621178   | Unique equipment identifier |
| `acquisition_date`   | Date     | Date the trailer was acquired by the company            | 2018-05-11          | Used for lifecycle tracking |
| `status`             | String   | Current operational status of the trailer               | Active              | May include statuses like Active, Maintenance, Retired |
| `current_location`   | String   | Current terminal or city where the trailer is located   | Kansas City         | Operational positioning data |

---

## Table: `customers`

**Description:**  
This table contains account, contract, and revenue information for company customers. Each row represents one customer account.

**Grain:**  
One row = one customer.

---

## Columns

| Column Name                | Data Type | Description                                                      | Example            | Notes |
|----------------------------|----------|------------------------------------------------------------------|--------------------|------|
| `customer_id`              | String   | Unique identifier assigned to each customer                      | CUST00001          | Primary key for this table |
| `customer_name`            | String   | Official business name of the customer                           | Metro Wholesale    | — |
| `customer_type`            | String   | Type of business relationship                                    | Dedicated          | Example values: Dedicated, Contract, Spot |
| `credit_terms_days`        | Integer  | Number of days allowed for invoice payment                       | 60                 | Financial agreement term |
| `primary_freight_type`     | String   | Main category of goods transported for the customer              | General            | Example values: Retail, Automotive, Food/Beverage, Electronics |
| `account_status`           | String   | Current status of the customer account                           | Active             | Example values: Active, Inactive |
| `contract_start_date`      | Date     | Date the customer contract or relationship began                 | 2020-02-20         | Used for tenure analysis |
| `annual_revenue_potential` | Integer  | Estimated annual revenue value of the customer account           | 985117             | Financial planning metric |

---

## Table: `facilities`

**Description:**  
This table contains location, capacity, and operational information for company facilities. Each row represents one facility.

**Grain:**  
One row = one facility.

---

## Columns

| Column Name        | Data Type | Description                                                     | Example                          | Notes |
|--------------------|----------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------|------|
| `facility_id`      | String   | Unique identifier assigned to each facility                     | FAC00001                         | Primary key for this table |
| `facility_name`    | String   | Official name of the facility                                   | Houston Distribution Center      | — |
| `facility_type`    | String   | Type of logistics facility                                      | Cross-Dock                       | Example values: Distribution Center, Warehouse, Terminal, Cross-Dock |
| `city`             | String   | City where the facility is located                              | Houston                          | — |
| `state`            | String   | US state abbreviation of the facility location                  | TX                               | Two-letter state code |
| `latitude`         | Decimal  | Geographic latitude of the facility                             | 29.7604                          | Used for mapping and routing analysis |
| `longitude`        | Decimal  | Geographic longitude of the facility                            | -95.3698                         | Used for mapping and routing analysis |
| `dock_doors`       | Integer  | Number of loading/unloading dock doors at the facility          | 125                              | Capacity indicator |
| `operating_hours`  | String   | Standard operating hours of the facility                        | 24/7                             | May include ranges such as 8AM-5PM |

---

## Table: `routes`

**Description:**  
This table contains standard route, distance, and pricing information for common transportation lanes. Each row represents one origin–destination route.

**Grain:**  
One row = one route between two cities.

---

## Columns

| Column Name               | Data Type | Description                                                      | Example        | Notes |
|---------------------------|----------|------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------|------|
| `route_id`                | String   | Unique identifier assigned to each route                         | RTE00001       | Primary key for this table |
| `origin_city`             | String   | City where the route begins                                      | Atlanta        | — |
| `origin_state`            | String   | US state abbreviation of the origin location                     | GA             | Two-letter state code |
| `destination_city`        | String   | City where the route ends                                        | Chicago        | — |
| `destination_state`       | String   | US state abbreviation of the destination location                 | IL             | Two-letter state code |
| `typical_distance_miles`  | Integer  | Standard distance between origin and destination in miles        | 677            | Used for planning and cost calculations |
| `base_rate_per_mile`      | Decimal  | Standard base transportation rate charged per mile               | 1.70           | Pricing metric |
| `fuel_surcharge_rate`     | Decimal  | Additional rate per mile to account for fuel cost fluctuations   | 0.19           | Variable cost component |
| `typical_transit_days`    | Integer  | Expected number of days to complete the route                    | 1              | Service level indicator |

---

## Table: `loads`

**Description:**  
This table contains shipment-level financial and operational details for customer freight movements. Each row represents one load (shipment).

**Grain:**  
One row = one load.

---

## Columns

| Column Name        | Data Type | Description                                               | Example          | Notes                          |
|-------------------|-----------|-----------------------------------------------------------|-----------------|--------------------------------|
| `load_id`          | String    | Unique identifier for each shipment                       | LOAD00000001    | Primary key                    |
| `customer_id`      | String    | Identifier of the customer moving the freight            | CUST00183       | Foreign key to `customers`     |
| `route_id`         | String    | Route assigned to the shipment                            | RTE00019        | Foreign key to `routes`        |
| `load_date`        | Date      | Date the load was scheduled                               | 2022-01-01      | —                              |
| `load_type`        | String    | Equipment type required                                   | Dry Van         | e.g., Dry Van, Refrigerated    |
| `weight_lbs`       | Integer   | Total shipment weight in pounds                           | 19178           | —                              |
| `pieces`           | Integer   | Number of freight pieces                                   | 13              | —                              |
| `revenue`          | Decimal   | Linehaul revenue earned                                   | 3045.23         | Excludes surcharges            |
| `fuel_surcharge`   | Decimal   | Fuel surcharge revenue                                     | 406.72          | —                              |
| `accessorial_charges` | Decimal | Additional fees (e.g., liftgate, detention)              | 100             | —                              |
| `load_status`      | String    | Current status of the shipment                             | Completed       | e.g., Completed, In Transit    |
| `booking_type`     | String    | Type of booking                                           | Spot            | e.g., Spot, Contract, Dedicated|

---

## Table: `trips`

**Description:**  
This table contains detailed operational trip information for each load, including vehicles, drivers, distances, and durations.

**Grain:**  
One row = one trip for a load.

---

## Columns

| Column Name               | Data Type | Description                                               | Example          | Notes                          |
|----------------------------|-----------|-----------------------------------------------------------|-----------------|--------------------------------|
| `trip_id`                  | String    | Unique identifier for each trip                            | TRIP00000001    | Primary key                    |
| `load_id`                  | String    | Identifier of the associated load                          | LOAD00000001    | Foreign key to `loads`         |
| `driver_id`                | String    | Driver assigned to the trip                                | DRV00117        | Foreign key to `drivers`       |
| `truck_id`                 | String    | Truck assigned to the trip                                  | TRK00035        | Foreign key to `trucks`        |
| `trailer_id`               | String    | Trailer assigned to the trip                                | TRL00167        | Foreign key to `trailers`      |
| `dispatch_date`            | Date      | Date trip was dispatched                                    | 2022-01-01      | —                              |
| `actual_distance_miles`    | Integer   | Distance actually traveled in miles                         | 1314            | —                              |
| `actual_duration_hours`    | Decimal   | Duration of the trip in hours                                | 26.2            | —                              |
| `fuel_gallons_used`        | Decimal   | Fuel used for the trip                                       | 183.8           | —                              |
| `average_mpg`              | Decimal   | Average fuel efficiency                                     | 7.15            | Calculated as distance / fuel  |
| `idle_time_hours`          | Decimal   | Total idle time during trip                                  | 3.5             | —                              |
| `trip_status`              | String    | Current status of the trip                                    | Completed       | e.g., Completed, In Progress   |

---

## Table: `fuel_purchases`

**Description:**  
This table tracks all fuel purchases for trips, including quantities, cost, and location.

**Grain:**  
One row = one fuel purchase.

---

## Columns

| Column Name          | Data Type | Description                                           | Example         | Notes                          |
|---------------------|-----------|-------------------------------------------------------|----------------|--------------------------------|
| `fuel_purchase_id`   | String    | Unique identifier for each fuel purchase             | FUEL00000001   | Primary key                    |
| `trip_id`            | String    | Trip associated with the fuel purchase               | TRIP00051284   | Foreign key to `trips`         |
| `truck_id`           | String    | Truck used for the fuel purchase                      | TRK00045       | Foreign key to `trucks`        |
| `driver_id`          | String    | Driver making the purchase                             | DRV00102       | Foreign key to `drivers`       |
| `purchase_date`      | Datetime  | Date and time of the fuel purchase                     | 2023-10-22 5:00:00 | —                          |
| `location_city`      | String    | City where fuel was purchased                           | Columbus       | —                              |
| `location_state`     | String    | State of fuel purchase location                        | MN             | Two-letter code                |
| `gallons`            | Decimal   | Number of gallons purchased                             | 131.6          | —                              |
| `price_per_gallon`   | Decimal   | Price per gallon paid                                    | 3.399          | —                              |
| `total_cost`         | Decimal   | Total cost of purchase                                   | 447.31         | —                              |
| `fuel_card_number`   | String    | Fuel card used                                          | FC567161       | —                              |

---

## Table: `maintenance_records`

**Description:**  
This table logs maintenance activities for trucks, including cost, labor, parts, and downtime.

**Grain:**  
One row = one maintenance event for a truck.

---

## Columns

| Column Name           | Data Type | Description                                         | Example       | Notes                          |
|----------------------|-----------|-----------------------------------------------------|---------------|--------------------------------|
| `maintenance_id`      | String    | Unique identifier for each maintenance event       | MAINT00000001 | Primary key                    |
| `truck_id`            | String    | Truck undergoing maintenance                        | TRK00085      | Foreign key to `trucks`        |
| `maintenance_date`    | Date      | Date maintenance occurred                            | 2022-01-01    | —                              |
| `maintenance_type`    | String    | Type of maintenance performed                        | Inspection    | e.g., Inspection, Repair       |
| `odometer_reading`    | Integer   | Truck mileage at time of maintenance                 | 400255        | —                              |
| `labor_hours`         | Decimal   | Labor hours spent                                     | 7.8           | —                              |
| `labor_cost`          | Decimal   | Cost of labor                                        | 781.42        | —                              |
| `parts_cost`          | Decimal   | Cost of parts used                                   | 10.41         | —                              |
| `total_cost`          | Decimal   | Total maintenance cost                                | 791.83        | labor + parts                  |
| `facility_location`   | String    | Facility where maintenance occurred                  | Kansas City   | —                              |
| `downtime_hours`      | Decimal   | Time truck was unavailable due to maintenance        | 22.2          | —                              |
| `service_description` | String    | Short description of the service performed          | Emergency Inspection | —                    |

---

## Table: `delivery_events`

**Description:**  
This table captures pickup and delivery events for each trip, including scheduled and actual times, locations, and delays.

**Grain:**  
One row = one delivery event (pickup or delivery) for a trip.

---

## Columns

| Column Name           | Data Type | Description                                         | Example         | Notes                          |
|-----------------------|-----------|-----------------------------------------------------|----------------|--------------------------------|
| `event_id`            | String    | Unique identifier for each event                    | EVT00000001    | Primary key                    |
| `load_id`             | String    | Associated load                                     | LOAD00000001   | Foreign key to `loads`         |
| `trip_id`             | String    | Associated trip                                     | TRIP00000001   | Foreign key to `trips`         |
| `event_type`          | String    | Type of event                                       | Pickup         | Pickup or Delivery             |
| `facility_id`         | String    | Facility associated with the event                  | FAC00034       | Foreign key to `facilities`    |
| `scheduled_datetime`  | Datetime  | Scheduled date and time for the event               | 2022-01-01 18:00:00 | —                     |
| `actual_datetime`     | Datetime  | Actual date and time the event occurred             | 2022-01-01 20:58:56 | —                     |
| `detention_minutes`   | Integer   | Delay duration in minutes                            | 0              | —                              |
| `on_time_flag`        | Boolean   | Indicator if event was on time                       | FALSE          | TRUE = on time                 |
| `location_city`       | String    | City where event occurred                             | Houston        | —                              |
| `location_state`      | String    | State where event occurred                            | TX             | Two-letter code                |

---

## Table: `safety_incidents`

**Description:**  
This table records safety and compliance incidents related to trips, trucks, and drivers.

**Grain:**  
One row = one incident.

---

## Columns

| Column Name             | Data Type | Description                                        | Example         | Notes                          |
|-------------------------|-----------|----------------------------------------------------|----------------|--------------------------------|
| `incident_id`           | String    | Unique identifier for the incident                | INC00000001    | Primary key                    |
| `trip_id`               | String    | Trip associated with the incident                 | TRIP00036079   | Foreign key to `trips`         |
| `truck_id`              | String    | Truck involved in the incident                     | TRK00006       | Foreign key to `trucks`        |
| `driver_id`             | String    | Driver involved in the incident                    | DRV00006       | Foreign key to `drivers`       |
| `incident_date`         | Datetime  | Date and time of the incident                      | 2023-04-09 14:00:00 | —                         |
| `incident_type`         | String    | Type of incident                                   | Moving Violation | e.g., Accident, DOT Violation |
| `location_city`         | String    | City where the incident occurred                   | Columbus        | —                              |
| `location_state`        | String    | State of the incident location                     | PA              | Two-letter code                |
| `at_fault_flag`         | Boolean   | Indicates if the driver was at fault               | TRUE            | —                              |
| `injury_flag`           | Boolean   | Indicates if there were injuries                   | FALSE           | —                              |
| `vehicle_damage_cost`   | Decimal   | Cost of vehicle damage                              | 12629.26        | —                              |
| `cargo_damage_cost`     | Decimal   | Cost of cargo damage                                | 0               | —                              |
| `claim_amount`          | Decimal   | Total claim amount filed                             | 12629.26        | —                              |
| `preventable_flag`      | Boolean   | Indicates if incident was preventable              | TRUE            | —                              |
| `description`           | String    | Short description of the incident                  | Severe incident involving equipment | — |

